BRAZIL DAYBOOK: Budget Balance, Oi, Renner, Rousseff at the WEF

-- B y   H e l d e r   M a r i n h o
-- 
2011-04-29T03:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-29/brazil-daybook-budget-balance-oi-renner-rousseff-at-the-wef.html
Brazil  probably posted a budget
deficit of 6.8 billion reais ($4.3 billion) in March, according
to a Bloomberg survey of three economists. The estimate is lower
than the deficit of 11.2 billion reais in February and 17.2
billion in March of last year.  WHAT TO WATCH:
*President  Dilma Rousseff  speaks at the Latin America edition of
the  World Economic Forum  in Rio de Janeiro. The event brings
together global business leaders, such as Citigroup’s Chief
Executive Officer Vikram Pandit and Brazilian billionaire Eike
Batista
*The central bank holds a press conference in Brasilia on the
budget balance figures for the month of March at 11 a.m.
*Banco Panamericano SA’s shareholders meet in Sao Paulo to
approve the bank 2010 earnings, at 2 p.m.
*Neoenergia SA to host meeting with investors in  Sao Paulo  at at
8:30 a.m.  EARNINGS:
*Eletrobras (ELET6 BZ), aft. mkt.  ECONOMY:
*Budget balance and net debt at 10:30 a.m.  EQUITIES:
*Vale (VALE5 BZ) bought stake in Brazil’s Belo Monte dam project
*CPFL (CPFE6 BZ) approved grouping and split of shares
*Panamericano (BPNM4 BZ) named Jose Luiz Acar Pedro chairman
*Lojas Renner (LREN4 BZ) posted first-quarter profit 47.6
Million Reais
*Magazine Luiza (MGLU3 BZ), holders raising 925.8 million reais
in IPO  MARKETS
*The Bovespa index fell 0.9 percent to 65,673.21.
*The real fell 0.7 percent to 1.5780 per dollar.  To contact the reporter on this story:
